- allocate a `List` to hold the substrings
- loop until the line is `blank` or if the remaining segment is less than `size`
- now check the character for spaces starting at size less 1. 
- Add that substring to the list and update the line to the next starting position.
```
public static List&lt;String&gt; splitLine(String line, int size) {
    List&lt;String&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
    while (!line.isBlank()) {
        int len = Math.min(line.length(), size);
        if (len &lt; size) {
            list.add(line);
            break;
        }
        while (line.charAt(--len) != &#39; &#39;) {
           if (len == 0) {
             throw new 
                 IllegalArgumentException(&quot;\nWord length exceeds size specification&quot;);
           }
        }
        list.add(line.substring(0, len));
        line = line.substring(len+1);
    }
    return list;
}

